CarND Advanced Lane Finding Project¶

Project Goals¶

The goals/steps of this project are the following:

  • Compute the camera calibration matrix and distortion coefficients given a set of chessboard images
  • Apply a distortion correction to raw images
  • Use color transforms, gradients, etc. to create a thresholded binary image
  • Apply a perspective transform to rectify binary image ("birds-eye view")
  • Detect lane pixels and fit to find the lane boundary
  • Determine the curvature of the lane and vehicle position with respect to center
  • Warp the detected lane boundaries back onto the original image
  • Output visual display of the lane boundaries and numerical estimation of lane curvature and vehicle position

import os
import glob
import cv2
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from moviepy.editor import VideoFileClip

# A helper class to calibrate the camera using OpenCV
class CameraCalibrater:
    def __init__(self, calibration_image_directory):
        self.calibration_image_directory = calibration_image_directory
        
        # Camera calibration properties, e.g. the object points, images points and etc.
        self.image_points = []
        self.object_points = []
        
        self.nx = 9
        self.ny = 6
        self.objp = np.zeros((self.nx * self.ny, 3), np.float32)
        self.objp[:, :2] = np.mgrid[0:self.nx, 0:self.ny].T.reshape(-1, 2)
        
        self.camera_matrix = None
        self.dist_coeffs = None
        
        # Drawing settings
        self.calibration_images = []
        self.images_with_corners = []
        self.image_rows = 5
        self.image_columns = 4
    
    # Show all the calibration images with the corners drawn on the chess board
    def show_chessboard_images(self):
        image_count = len(self.images_with_corners)
        fig, axes = plt.subplots(self.image_rows, self.image_columns, figsize=(15,13))
        indexes = range(self.image_columns * self.image_rows)
        for ax, index in zip(axes.flat, indexes):
            if (index < image_count):
                image = self.images_with_corners[index]
                ax.imshow(image)
                ax.set_title('Calibration Image {0}'.format(index + 1))
    
    # Find and draw the corners on the chess board
    def draw_chessboard_coners(self):
        camera_calibration_image_files = os.listdir(self.calibration_image_directory)
        for image_file_name in camera_calibration_image_files:
            image_path = os.path.join(self.calibration_image_directory, image_file_name)
            image = cv2.imread(image_path)
            self.calibration_images.append(image)
            gray_image = cv2.cvtColor(image, cv2.COLOR_BGR2GRAY)
            corner_found, corners = cv2.findChessboardCorners(gray_image, (self.nx, self.ny), None)
            if (corner_found):
                self.image_points.append(corners)
                self.object_points.append(self.objp)
                cv2.drawChessboardCorners(image, (self.nx,self.ny), corners, corner_found)
                self.images_with_corners.append(image)
        
        self.images_with_corners.extend(self.images_with_corners[-3:])
    
    # Calibrate the camera
    def calibrate_camera(self):
        gray_image = cv2.cvtColor(self.calibration_images[0], cv2.COLOR_BGR2GRAY)
        ret, self.camera_matrix, self.dist_coeffs, rvecs, tvecs = \
            cv2.calibrateCamera(self.object_points, self.image_points, gray_image.shape, None, None)
    
    # Get the undistorted image of the original image
    def get_undistorted_image_from_path(self, original_image_path):
        original_image = cv2.imread(original_image_path)
        return self.get_undistorted_image(original_image)
    
    # Get the undistorted image of the original image
    def get_undistorted_image(self, original_image):
        undistorted_image = cv2.undistort(original_image, \
            self.camera_matrix, self.dist_coeffs, None, self.camera_matrix)
        return undistorted_image
    
    # Show the undistorted image together with the original image
    def show_undistorted_image(self, original_image_path):
        original_image = cv2.imread(original_image_path)
        plt.figure(figsize=(20, 16))
        plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)
        plt.title('The Original Image')
        plt.imshow(original_image[:, :, ::-1])
        
        undistorted_image = self.get_undistorted_image_from_path(original_image_path)
        plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)
        plt.title('The Undistorted Image')
        plt.imshow(undistorted_image[:, :, ::-1])
        plt.show()

Creating Thresholded Binary Images¶

In [5]:
# A helper class to generate binray images using thresholds
class BinaryImageGenerator:
    def __init__(self):
        self.LAB_threshs = {'L':(0,255), 'A':(0,255), 'B':(155,255)}
        self.RGB_threshs = {'R':(177,255), 'G':(177,255), 'B':(177,255)}
    
    def generate(self, image):
        binary_image_from_LAB = self.generate_from_LAB_image(image)
        binary_image_from_RGB = self.generate_from_RGB_image(image)
        binary_image = np.zeros_like(binary_image_from_LAB)
        binary_image[(binary_image_from_LAB == 1) | (binary_image_from_RGB == 1)] = 1
        return binary_image
    
    def generate_from_RGB_image(self, image):
        blurred_image = cv2.GaussianBlur(image, (5,5), 2.0)
        R_binary_image = self.generate_from_RGB_channel(blurred_image, 'R', self.RGB_threshs['R'])
        G_binary_image = self.generate_from_RGB_channel(blurred_image, 'G', self.RGB_threshs['G'])
        B_binary_image = self.generate_from_RGB_channel(blurred_image, 'B', self.RGB_threshs['B'])
        binary_image = np.zeros_like(R_binary_image)
        binary_image[(R_binary_image == 1) & (G_binary_image == 1) & (B_binary_image == 1)] = 1
        return binary_image
    
    def generate_from_RGB_channel(self, image, channel, thresh):
        if (channel == 'B'):
            channel_index = 0
        elif (channel == 'G'):
            channel_index = 1
        else:
            channel_index = 2
        
        channel_image = image[:, :, channel_index]
        binary_image = np.zeros_like(channel_image)
        binary_image[(channel_image >= thresh[0]) & (channel_image <= thresh[1])] = 1
        return binary_image
    
    def generate_from_LAB_image(self, image):
        blurred_image = cv2.GaussianBlur(image, (5,5), 2.0)
        L_binary_image = self.generate_from_LAB_channel(blurred_image, 'L', self.LAB_threshs['L'])
        A_binary_image = self.generate_from_LAB_channel(blurred_image, 'A', self.LAB_threshs['A'])
        B_binary_image = self.generate_from_LAB_channel(blurred_image, 'B', self.LAB_threshs['B'])
        binary_image = np.zeros_like(B_binary_image)
        binary_image[(L_binary_image == 1) & (A_binary_image == 1) & (B_binary_image == 1)] = 1
        return binary_image
    
    def generate_from_LAB_channel(self, image, channel, thresh):
        LAB_image = cv2.cvtColor(image, cv2.COLOR_BGR2Lab)
        if (channel == 'L'):
            channel_index = 0
        elif (channel == 'A'):
            channel_index = 1
        else:
            channel_index = 2
        
        channel_image = LAB_image[:, :, channel_index]
        binary_image = np.zeros_like(channel_image)
        binary_image[(channel_image >= thresh[0]) & (channel_image <= thresh[1])] = 1
        return binary_image

# A helper class to warp a image
class ImageWarper:
    def __init__(self, image_shape=(720, 1280)):
        self.image_shape = (image_shape[1], image_shape[0])
        
        self.source_matrix = np.float32([[585, 455], \
                                         [705, 455], \
                                         [1130, self.image_shape[1]], \
                                         [190, self.image_shape[1]]])
        self.destination_matrix = np.float32([[200, 0], \
                                              [self.image_shape[0] - 200, 0], \
                                              [self.image_shape[0] - 200, self.image_shape[1]], \
                                              [200, self.image_shape[1]]])
        
        self.transform = cv2.getPerspectiveTransform(self.source_matrix, \
                                                     self.destination_matrix)
        self.reversed_transform = cv2.getPerspectiveTransform(self.destination_matrix, \
                                                              self.source_matrix)
    
    # Get the warped image from the input image
    def get_warped_image(self, image):
        warped_image = cv2.warpPerspective(image, self.transform, self.image_shape, flags=cv2.INTER_LINEAR)
        return warped_image

Lane Detection¶

In [9]:
# A helper class to detect the lane in a warped binary image
class LaneDetector:
    def __init__(self):
        self.reset()
    
    # Reset all the properties of this lane detector
    def reset(self):
        self.warped_binary_image = None
        self.output_image = None
        
        # Meters per pixel in x dimension
        self.x_meters_per_pix = 3.7 / 700
        
        # Meters per pixel in y dimension
        self.y_meters_per_pix = 30 / 720
        
        self.nwindows = 9
        
        self.left_fit = None
        self.right_fit = None
        
        self.last_realible_left_fit = None
        self.last_realible_right_fit = None
        
        self.left_fit_meters = None
        self.right_fit_meters = None
    
    # Detect the lanes line in the binary image
    def detect_lane(self):
        histogram = np.sum(self.warped_binary_image[self.warped_binary_image.shape[0]//2:, :], axis=0)
        self.output_image = np.dstack((self.warped_binary_image, self.warped_binary_image, self.warped_binary_image))
        self.output_image = np.uint8(self.output_image * 255)
        self.output_image = 255 * self.output_image

        midpoint = histogram.shape[0]//2
        left_base = np.argmax(histogram[:midpoint])
        right_base = np.argmax(histogram[midpoint:]) + midpoint
        
        window_height = np.int(self.warped_binary_image.shape[0] / self.nwindows)

        # Identify the x and y positions of all nonzero pixels in the image
        nonzero = self.warped_binary_image.nonzero()
        nonzeroy = np.array(nonzero[0])
        nonzerox = np.array(nonzero[1])

        left_current = left_base
        right_current = right_base
        margin = 80
        minpix = 55
        left_lane_inds = []
        right_lane_inds = []

        for window in range(self.nwindows):
            win_y_low = self.warped_binary_image.shape[0] - ((window + 1) * window_height)
            win_y_high = self.warped_binary_image.shape[0] - (window * window_height)
            win_xleft_low = left_current - margin
            win_xleft_high = left_current + margin
            win_xright_low = right_current - margin
            win_xright_high = right_current + margin

            cv2.rectangle(self.output_image, (win_xleft_low,win_y_low), \
                          (win_xleft_high,win_y_high), (0,255,0), 2)
            cv2.rectangle(self.output_image, (win_xright_low,win_y_low), \
                          (win_xright_high,win_y_high), (0,255,0), 2)

            good_left_inds = ((nonzeroy >= win_y_low) & \
                              (nonzeroy < win_y_high) & \
                              (nonzerox >= win_xleft_low) & \
                              (nonzerox < win_xleft_high)).nonzero()[0]

            good_right_inds = ((nonzeroy >= win_y_low) & \
                               (nonzeroy < win_y_high) & \
                               (nonzerox >= win_xright_low) & \
                               (nonzerox < win_xright_high)).nonzero()[0]

            # Append these indices to the lists
            left_lane_inds.append(good_left_inds)
            right_lane_inds.append(good_right_inds)

            # If we found more than minpix pixels, recenter next window on their mean position
            if (len(good_left_inds) > minpix):
                left_current = np.int(np.mean(nonzerox[good_left_inds]))

            if (len(good_right_inds) > minpix):
                right_current = np.int(np.mean(nonzerox[good_right_inds]))

        left_lane_inds = np.concatenate(left_lane_inds)
        right_lane_inds = np.concatenate(right_lane_inds)

        leftx = nonzerox[left_lane_inds]
        lefty = nonzeroy[left_lane_inds] 
        rightx = nonzerox[right_lane_inds]
        righty = nonzeroy[right_lane_inds] 

        try:
            # Fit the polynomial
            self.left_fit = np.polyfit(lefty, leftx, 2)
            self.right_fit = np.polyfit(righty, rightx, 2)
            
            # Fit the polynomial using meters
            self.left_fit_meters = np.polyfit(lefty*self.y_meters_per_pix, leftx*self.x_meters_per_pix, 2)
            self.right_fit_meters = np.polyfit(righty*self.y_meters_per_pix, rightx*self.x_meters_per_pix, 2)
        except TypeError:
            pass
        
        self.output_image[nonzeroy[left_lane_inds], nonzerox[left_lane_inds]] = [255, 0, 0]
        self.output_image[nonzeroy[right_lane_inds], nonzerox[right_lane_inds]] = [0, 0, 255]
    
    # Draw the original binary image with the lane lines detected
    def draw_image_with_lane(self):
        ploty = np.linspace(0, self.warped_binary_image.shape[0]-1, self.warped_binary_image.shape[0])
        left_fitx = (self.left_fit[0]*ploty**2) + (self.left_fit[1]*ploty) + self.left_fit[2]
        right_fitx = (self.right_fit[0]*ploty**2) + (self.right_fit[1]*ploty) + self.right_fit[2]
        
        fig = plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
        plt.imshow(self.output_image)
        plt.plot(left_fitx, ploty, color='yellow')
        plt.plot(right_fitx, ploty, color='yellow')
        plt.xlim(0, 1280)
        plt.ylim(720, 0)
        plt.show()
    
    # Check if this detector has already detected lane
    def has_realible_detection(self):
        if ((self.last_realible_left_fit is not None) and \
            (self.last_realible_right_fit is not None)):
            return True
        else:
            return False
    
    # Do sanity check on the lane detection
    def do_sanity_check(self):
        if ((len(self.left_fit) < 3) or (len(self.right_fit) < 3)):
            return False

        ploty = np.linspace(0, 720, 30)
        leftx = self.left_fit[0]*ploty**2 + self.left_fit[1]*ploty + self.left_fit[2]
        rightx = self.right_fit[0]*ploty**2 + self.right_fit[1]*ploty + self.right_fit[2]
        
        mean_dist = np.mean(rightx - leftx)
        dmin = np.min(rightx - leftx)
        dmax = np.max(rightx - leftx)
        if ((mean_dist >= 550) and (mean_dist <= 750)):
            status = True
        else:
            return False
        
        if (dmax - dmin <= 80):
            status = True
        else:
            return False
        
        # Calualuate the slope of some random selected points and compare them
        slope_left = 2*self.left_fit[0]*ploty + self.left_fit[1]
        slope_right = 2*self.right_fit[0]*ploty + self.right_fit[1]
        if (np.mean(np.abs(slope_left - slope_right)) < 0.12):
            status = True
        else:
            return False
    
        # Decide if we should use calculated points
        if (status):
            self.last_realible_left_fit = self.left_fit
            self.last_realible_right_fit = self.right_fit
        else:
            # Use the last realible fit
            self.left_fit = self.last_realible_left_fit
            self.right_fit = self.last_realible_right_fit
        
        return status

    # Detect the lanes line in next image
    def detect_lane_in_next_image(self, plot=True):
        nonzero = self.warped_binary_image.nonzero()
        nonzeroy = np.array(nonzero[0])
        nonzerox = np.array(nonzero[1])
        margin = 80
        left_lane_inds = ((nonzerox > (self.left_fit[0]*(nonzeroy**2) + \
                                       self.left_fit[1]*nonzeroy + \
                                       self.left_fit[2] - margin)) & 
                          (nonzerox < (self.left_fit[0]*(nonzeroy**2) + \
                                       self.left_fit[1]*nonzeroy + \
                                       self.left_fit[2] + margin))) 
        right_lane_inds = ((nonzerox > (self.right_fit[0]*(nonzeroy**2) + \
                                        self.right_fit[1]*nonzeroy + \
                                        self.right_fit[2] - margin)) & 
                           (nonzerox < (self.right_fit[0]*(nonzeroy**2) + \
                                        self.right_fit[1]*nonzeroy + \
                                        self.right_fit[2] + margin)))  

        # Extract left and right line pixel positions
        leftx = nonzerox[left_lane_inds]
        lefty = nonzeroy[left_lane_inds] 
        rightx = nonzerox[right_lane_inds]
        righty = nonzeroy[right_lane_inds]
        
        # Fit a second order polynomial to each
        self.left_fit = np.polyfit(lefty, leftx, 2)
        self.right_fit = np.polyfit(righty, rightx, 2)
        
        # Fit the polynomial using meters
        self.left_fit_meters = np.polyfit(lefty*self.y_meters_per_pix, leftx*self.x_meters_per_pix, 2)
        self.right_fit_meters = np.polyfit(righty*self.y_meters_per_pix, rightx*self.x_meters_per_pix, 2)

Lane Information Text Rendering¶

# A helper class to render the lane information text into the image
class LaneTextRenderer:
    def __init__(self, reversed_transform):
        # Meters per pixel in x dimension
        self.x_meters_per_pix = 3.7 / 700
        
        # Meters per pixel in y dimension
        self.y_meters_per_pix = 30 / 720
        
        self.reversed_transform = reversed_transform
        
        self.left_fit = None
        self.right_fit = None
        
        self.left_fit_meters = None
        self.right_fit_meters = None
    
    # Get curverature of the lane lines
    def get_curverature(self, image_shape):
        ploty = np.linspace(0, image_shape[0]-1, num=image_shape[0])
        
        # Fit new polynomials to x,y in world space
        y_max = np.max(ploty)
        leftx = self.left_fit[0]*ploty**2 + self.left_fit[1]*ploty + self.left_fit[2]
        rightx = self.right_fit[0]*ploty**2 + self.right_fit[1]*ploty + self.right_fit[2]

        left_fit_cr = np.polyfit(ploty * self.y_meters_per_pix, leftx * self.x_meters_per_pix, 2)
        right_fit_cr = np.polyfit(ploty * self.y_meters_per_pix, rightx * self.x_meters_per_pix, 2)

        # Calculate the radius of curvature
        left_radius_of_curvature = ((1 + (2*left_fit_cr[0]*y_max*self.y_meters_per_pix + \
                                          left_fit_cr[1])**2)**1.5) \
                                    / np.absolute(2*left_fit_cr[0])
        right_radius_of_curvature = ((1 + (2*right_fit_cr[0]*y_max*self.y_meters_per_pix + \
                                           right_fit_cr[1])**2)**1.5) \
                                    / np.absolute(2*right_fit_cr[0])
        
        # Calculate the offset using meters
        x_meters_max = image_shape[1] * self.x_meters_per_pix
        y_meters_max = image_shape[0] * self.y_meters_per_pix
        
        line_left_meters = self.left_fit_meters[0]*y_meters_max**2 + \
                           self.left_fit_meters[1]*y_meters_max + self.left_fit_meters[2]
        line_right_meters = self.right_fit_meters[0]*y_meters_max**2 + \
                            self.right_fit_meters[1]*y_meters_max + self.right_fit_meters[2]
        line_middle_meters = line_left_meters + ((line_right_meters - line_left_meters) / 2)
        
        vehicle_center_meters = x_meters_max / 2
        car_offset = line_middle_meters - vehicle_center_meters
        
        return left_radius_of_curvature, right_radius_of_curvature, car_offset
    
    # Render the lane information text into the image
    def render_lane_text(self, image):
        left_radius_of_curvature, right_radius_of_curvature, car_offset = self.get_curverature(image.shape)
        radius_of_curvature = (left_radius_of_curvature + right_radius_of_curvature) / 2
        font = cv2.FONT_HERSHEY_SIMPLEX
        cv2.putText(image, 'Radius of Curvature: %d(m)' % (radius_of_curvature), \
                    (50, 50), font, 1, (255, 255, 255), 2)
        
        direction = 'left'
        if (car_offset < 0):
            direction = 'right'
        
        cv2.putText(image, ('Vehicle is %.2fm %s of the center' % (np.abs(car_offset), direction)), \
                    (50, 100), font, 1, (255, 255, 255), 2)
        
        image = cv2.cvtColor(image, cv2.COLOR_RGB2BGR)
        return image
    
    # Warp the lane information text into the image
    def do_reverse_warp(self, image, warped_image):
        warp_zero = np.zeros_like(warped_image).astype(np.uint8)
        color_warp = np.dstack((warp_zero, warp_zero, warp_zero))
        ploty = np.linspace(0, image.shape[0]-1, image.shape[0])
        
        leftx = self.left_fit[0]*ploty**2 + self.left_fit[1]*ploty + self.left_fit[2]
        rightx = self.right_fit[0]*ploty**2 + self.right_fit[1]*ploty + self.right_fit[2]
        
        pts_left = np.array([np.transpose(np.vstack([leftx, ploty]))])
        pts_right = np.array([np.flipud(np.transpose(np.vstack([rightx, ploty])))])
        pts = np.hstack((pts_left, pts_right))

        # Draw the lane onto the warped blank image
        cv2.fillPoly(color_warp, np.int_([pts]), (0, 255, 0))

        # Warp the blank back to original image space using reversed perspective matrix
        new_warped_image = cv2.warpPerspective(color_warp, self.reversed_transform, (image.shape[1], image.shape[0]))

        # Combine the result with the original image
        result = cv2.addWeighted(image, 1, new_warped_image, 0.3, 0)
        return result
    
    def show_image_with_lane_text(self, original_image, warped_image):
        plt.figure(figsize=(20, 16))
        plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)
        plt.title('Original Image')
        plt.imshow(original_image[:, :, ::-1])
        
        left_radius_of_curvature, right_radius_of_curvature, car_offset = self.get_curverature(original_image.shape)
        result = self.do_reverse_warp(original_image, warped_image)
        
        font = cv2.FONT_HERSHEY_SIMPLEX
        radius_of_curvature = (left_radius_of_curvature + right_radius_of_curvature) / 2
        cv2.putText(result, 'Radius of Curvature: %d(m)' % (radius_of_curvature), \
                    (50, 50), font, 1.5, (255, 255, 255), 2)
        
        direction = 'left'
        if (car_offset <= 0):
            direction = 'right'
        
        cv2.putText(result, ('Vehicle is %.2fm %s of the center' % (np.abs(car_offset), direction)), \
                    (50, 100), font, 1.5, (255, 255, 255), 2)
        plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)
        plt.title('Image with Lane Detection')
        plt.imshow(result[:, :, ::-1])
        plt.show()

Video Production¶

1. Create the Image Processor¶

In [13]:
# A global lane detector used by the image processor
global_lane_detector = LaneDetector()

# A image processor used to produce videos
def image_processor(image):
    RGB_image = cv2.cvtColor(image, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)
    undistorted_image = camera_calibrater.get_undistorted_image(RGB_image)
    binary_image = binary_image_generator.generate(undistorted_image)
    warped_image = cv2.warpPerspective(binary_image, image_warper.transform, \
        (RGB_image.shape[1], RGB_image.shape[0]), \
        flags=cv2.INTER_LINEAR)
    
    global_lane_detector.warped_binary_image = warped_image
    if (not global_lane_detector.has_realible_detection()):
        global_lane_detector.detect_lane()
    else:
        try:
            global_lane_detector.detect_lane_in_next_image(plot = False)
        except TypeError:
            pass
    
    # Do sanity check
    global_lane_detector.do_sanity_check()
    
    # Render the lane information text onto the image
    lane_text_renderer = LaneTextRenderer(image_warper.reversed_transform)
    lane_text_renderer.left_fit = global_lane_detector.left_fit
    lane_text_renderer.right_fit = global_lane_detector.right_fit
    lane_text_renderer.left_fit_meters = global_lane_detector.left_fit_meters
    lane_text_renderer.right_fit_meters = global_lane_detector.right_fit_meters
    
    image_with_lane = lane_text_renderer.do_reverse_warp(undistorted_image, warped_image)
    image_with_lane_text = lane_text_renderer.render_lane_text(image_with_lane)
    return image_with_lane_text
